<h2>You clicked on a simulated phishing test.</h2>

<h3>Here are some tips to help you stay safer in the future</h3>
</div>

<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-4">
<h1>Tip: #1</h1>

<h2>Check the URL Carefully</h2>
Always hover over links before clicking and ensure the URL looks legitimate. Look out for subtle misspellings or unusual domain extensions</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
<h1>Tip: #2</h1>

<h2>Be Suspicious</h2>
Never open email attachment or links unless you&#39;re expecting them, even the email seems to come from someone you know. Phishing often uses infected files to install malware</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
<h1>Tip: #3</h1>

<h2>Verify the Sender</h2>
If you&#39;re unsure about an email, verify the sender by contacting them through official channels (don&#39;t use the contact information from the email)</div>

